 that are mostly made up of multi boxers. Also, I see it in groups a lot more now. Grouping with a multi boxer, to me, sucks. No talking, no notta. Especially grouping in the Planes. Anyway, just wanted to know your opinion.<br>
<br>
Idyaar Dardaman<br>
High Priest of Vazaelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bedey>bedey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/30/03 10:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4212.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multi box players</span><hr size=1> I did until I slowed down (semi-quit) EQ, I did it, because no one really was in to questing and tradeskills like I was, so when I needed it, I had it there. I could farm easier, stay longer to get items (more room), plus for faction farming with a tank, even greens wear your down some, so you need heals once in a blue, its quicker.<br>
<br>
And then when I wanted to grind, and groups were scarce ( I played weird hours ) I had one.<br>
<br>
I will two box again, im looking at it for E&amp;B and Horizons. <p>Bladelorn Greystalker -- 52 Ranger Bish<br>
