Falelorn -- 58 War Retired</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kamidari>Kamidari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(5/31/03 12:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4212.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multi box players</span><hr size=1> I 2-box because I wanted a better pet for my shaman, so I made a warrior.  It just makes 'soloing' a lot easier for me, and I don't find it to be very hard to do.  In fact, I feel kind of strange now when I'm not 2-boxing...  Not enough to do or something. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bhumpatta>BhumPatta</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/1/03 6:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4212.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multi box players</span><hr size=1> I have a few low level twinks that I PL with my shaman once in a while.  With the second toon there I find that I can actually talk more as I end up doing less with my shaman.  Its amazing how much more you can say when you don't have to mash that cani 4 button every six seconds, though bards still have it worse.   <p>&quot;Dude, wheres my car?&quot; not winning an Academy Award was a conspiracy.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vazsepha>Vaz Sepha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/2/03 1:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4212.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Multi box players</span><hr size=1> It depends on the skill of the 2-boxer.. some I've grouped with are terrible, but the one I group with regularly, I prefer as my rogue/slower for group. As far as talking less.. I don't notice <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  I'm usually the quiet one in the group. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.edenproject.org/~elafount/sepha/images/gallery/sephasig2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
