</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eslizarde>ESLizarde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lurker</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/2/03 3:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4212.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Multi box players</span><hr size=1> I 2-box when I want to get some exp and don't want to bother LFG, or just plan to be on a short time.  I won't 2-box in exp groups or raids, because I use a KVM switch for my keyboard and it makes it tricky to move around sometimes, plus I'd rather focus my attention on one character in groups/raids.  When I 2-box I can just park my cleric in some relatively safe corner and pull to that spot, at which point I only have to click a couple of buttons to cast a heal as needed.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maldanonvaz>Maldan On Vaz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>New User</span><br>  Posts: 20<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/3/03 10:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4212.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> 2 boxing</span><hr size=1> I am breaking some rules here by posting but I have added a few posts over the last couple weeks so I am pretty much just exposing myself here. Please feel free to ban me as I dont deserve to be posting on these message boards but my 2 cents on 2 boxing.<br>
<br>
Me 2 Boxing: I would play at least 2 characters by myself all of the time, it made leveling a lot easier and it made farming a hell of a lot weirder. Plus I could stay on the downlow while I leveled up. I know talking is cool in EQ but sometimes I did not mind being by myself doing things on my own, especially when it was very hard to find groups, let alone good groups. Plus you have to admit that when you are with yourself you only have to do things for yourself and rely on yourself. You have to pee? Just go and come back, wanna eat something? See my point, you didnt have to wait and put a group together or go somewhere only to have half the group abandon you.<br>
<br>
Once you reach the point when you are in a guild that you call home finding groups usually isnt too hard and you can usually have friends who usually group with you. But its always nice to know that you can always go and do things on your own.<br>
<br>
Others 2 boxing: It totally depends on whos doing it because there are different types of people who multi box. There are those who are good at it, those who aren't and those who are sooo used to playing by themselves they have no idea how to function in a group with even one character. But for the most part I find players that two box to usually be oustanding players. They know their classes, the game, and know neat tricks. Its nice to know that you can pick up 2+ characters for a group just by asking one person and a lot of times that one person can play those 2+ characters better than those who just play their normal one.<br>
<br>
EX: Tsunnami was someone who really couldnt play his ONE character at times.<br>
<br>
Khar/Khareth was actually a better player than most monks/enchanters. It all depends on the player.<br>
<br>
-Mioshi <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1022<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/4/03 5:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4212.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 2 boxing</span><hr size=1> It also depends on class combination.  I have 3 65's on 3 different accounts (cleric, wizard, enchanter).  I can play wiz/cleric or wiz/chanter in just about any situation just as well as i could play them alone.  However, in difficult groups, I'm not fond of playing ench/cleric.  If you're talking sebilis, then sure, np.  However, I have 2 boxed cleric/chanter in PoEarth with a fast pulling group, and it got ugly at times when there were large pulls or mez resists.  I try to avoid that combination unless the ench is just a slower or I have great backup heals etc.<br>
<br>
I routinely 2 box cleric and wizard on raids (cleric more than ench because it's just more needed).  I don't find it to be particularly difficult except in a few rare cases (usually those that involve a lot of moving separately on each toon).<br>
